This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and the effectiveness of pretrained language models for capturing knowledge. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related topics. The paper also proposes a new pretraining objective, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper evaluates the model's performance on downstream tasks, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and neural networks (cs.NE).
